  "text": "The Internet of today has difficulties to support the increasing demand for resources and one of the reasons is related to the restricted evolution of the TCP/IP architecture since the 80s. More specifically, the evolution of the layers 3 and 4, as discussed in [CITATION_1] . The commercial usage of Internet and IP networks was a considerable obstacle to the improvements in the intermediate layers in this architecture.",
